 ZAP 1. n. Spiciness. 2. v. To make food spicy. 3. v. To make someone
"suffer" by making his food spicy. (Most hackers love spicy food.
Hot-and-sour soup is considered wimpy unless it makes you blow your nose for
the rest of the meal.) 4. ZAPPED adj. Spicy. This term is used to distinguish
between food that is hot (in temperature) and food that is "hot", that is,
spicy. For example, the Chinese appetizer Bon Bon Chicken is a kind of
chicken salad that is cold but zapped. see also ORIENTAL FOOD, LASER CHICKEN.